First, 16 artificial methylomes were created as references by merging single-cell methylomes of each neuronal cell type identified in a previous study [21]. Then, the simulated methylomes were generated by mixing the reference methylomes with random proportions. In each simulation, 100 methylomes were synthesized, based on which virtual methylome dissection was performed using the profiles of the eigen-pCSM loci in these 100 methylomes. To identify cell components from the dissection results, clustering analysis was performed on the dissected LMCs and 16 reference neuronal cell types, and the LMCs unambiguously matched to one of the reference neuronal cell types were considered to be recognized. The RMSE between LMCs and their matched reference methylomes was calculated to evaluate the recovery of reference methylomes by the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
